article.description: Garret Covington scored 25 points Thursday night and Western Illinois made a program-record 18 3-pointers to open Summit League play with a 93-91 win over Fort Wayne.
article.headline: Western Illinois sinks 18 3s, beats Fort Wayne 93-91
article.linkText: Western Illinois sinks 18 3s, beats Fort Wayne 93-91
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. -- Garret Covington scored 25 points Thursday night and Western Illinois made a program-record 18 3-pointers to open Summit League play with a 93-91 win over Fort Wayne. The Leathernecks (4-8, 1-0) made 18 of 37 3-point attempts led by C.J. Duff who made 7 of 9 from distance and finished with 21 points. Western Illinois took the lead for good at 79-76 on Mike Miklusak's 3 with 5:04 left and held on despite leading by no more than five the rest of the way. Brandon Gilbeck's free throws made it 93-88 with 13 seconds left. Miklusak added 17 points and 11 boards. The Mastodons (10-4, 0-1) took their first lead late in the first half and extended to their largest lead after the break at 58-50 before the Leathernecks went on a 19-2 run and had their widest margin at 69-60 with 9:22 to go. Mo Evans had 24 points for Fort Wayne.
